KW  - Trend analysis
AB  - Currently, generative artificial intelligence (GAI) has seen widespread penetration and advancement in educational management. However, systematic and comprehensive analyses of its integration into educational management are scarce. This study employs bibliometric analysis supplemented by visualization tools to conduct multi-dimensional statistical analyses of 506 valid studies retrieved from the Web of Science database, aiming to depict the current research status and evolutionary trends of GAI in educational management. Through quantitative analysis, four key findings are derived: first, publication volumes have grown annually and are poised to emerge as a key research hotspot; second, GAI exhibits a dual nature in educational management applications, with no clear predominance of merits over demerits; third, within educational management, research focus is most pronounced in university administrative scenarios, while cross-domain collaboration across subfields requires enhancement; fourth, future research will center on GAI tool innovation and intelligent educational management. Theoretically, this study delineates the research trajectory of GAI applications in educational management, offering data-backed support and decision-making insights for the formulation of relevant policies and practical implementation of GAI in educational management practices.
