KW  - Artificial Intelligence
KW  - Generative artificial intelligence
KW  - Nursing education
KW  - Nursing students
KW  - Post-secondary
KW  - Scoping review
AB  - Background
In post-secondary institutions, Generative Artificial Intelligence (GAI) is a growing area of interest and concern. However, knowledge about how nursing students use GAI to support their education is lacking.
Aim
This scoping review synthesizes existing literature on the use of GAI by nursing students in their post-secondary education.
Methods
A scoping review was conducted using Arksey and O’Malley’s (2005) framework and the Scoping Reviews (PRISMA-ScR) Checklist. Guiding questions included: How are nursing students using GAI in their programs? What concerns do they have with using GAI in their programs? What recommendations do nursing students have for using GAI in their programs?
Results
We identified six themes in the literature: critical thinking, educational support, ethics, the accuracy of GAI information, application of GAI, and recommendations for GAI use. The findings indicate that, while students see potential benefits in GAI for educational support, significant concerns persist around its impact on critical thinking and ethical use.
Conclusion
The review may inform nursing programs, educators, and post-secondary institutions on facilitating student success while upholding academic integrity.
