AB  - Generative artificial intelligence (GenAI) wields enormous potential to transform the built environment. The creative cognitive ability of GenAI to generate realistic content promises to provide a disruptive alternative solution to boost innovation, productivity and efficiency in the built environment. However, the industry is shrouded with uncertainties about the prospects and socioeconomic implications of GenAI. Hence, to unshroud these uncertainties, this study adopted a three-phase approach. Firstly, the study presented a state-of-the-art analysis of current applications and use case scenarios of GenAI models in the built environment. Secondly, the study employed multiple python libraries to analyse the sentiments of built environment professionals about the adoption of GenAI in the built environment. Thirdly, the study conducted a focus group study to determine the contextual layers behind the sentiments analyzed. The study evaluated 10 GenAI models and identified four to be mature for use in the built environment. The sentiment analysis revealed that 76% of professionals expressed positive sentiments about the adoption of GenAI, 8.5% were negative and 15.5% were neutral. The focus study identified ‘potential to save time and reduce’, ‘innovation and dynamism in built environment output’, ‘broader diversity of job creation in the built environment’, ‘opportunities for partnerships and collaborations’, and ‘enhanced company reputation’ as the contextual layers behind the positive sentiments of the professionals analyzed. These constituted the positive socioeconomic implications. Furthermore, the study identified ‘perception of potential white collar job losses’ among mid to top level management workers as the biggest threat to the adoption of GenAI in the built environment. This study makes a significant contribution to the body of knowledge by being the foremost study in built environment research to analyse the sentiments of built environment professionals about the adoption of GenAI. Findings from this study provide comprehensive depth of understanding into the current state-of-the-art of GenAI and its potential to augment the capabilities of professionals in the built environment. For policy and corporate decision-making, findings of the socioeconomic implications of GenAI would be valuable for informed policy drafting and corporate evaluations of GenAI adoption. Lastly, the study proposes a viable strategy for the adoption of GenAI in the built environment which serves as a guide for further deliberation on GenAI adoption and diffusion in the built environment.
